title: Car crashes down bank in Khandallah, Wellington
text:
Car crashes down bank in Khandallah, Wellington Last updated 20:35, February 7 2017 ROSS GIBLIN/ FAIRFAX NZ 
The 18-year-old driver of the car was unhurt in the crash. 
A car has crashed down down a bank in Onslow Rd, in the Wellington suburb of Khandallah. 
The incident happened shortly after 7pm on Tuesday, when the car skidded while travelling down a hill, and crashed through a barrier. 
The 18-year-old driver, who did not want to be named, was the only person in the car, and was not injured. ROSS GIBLIN/ FAIRFAX NZ 
Police and fire examine the scene of the crash, in Onslow Rd. 
She managed to get out out of the passenger door herself, and climb back up the bank to the road.
